                "name": "Case: two creatures",
                "type": "entries",
                "entries": [
                    "This new creature possess the abilities and features of both targets. You can designate which Base Values, innate bonuses, natural bonuses, and other abilities come from which target. For example, if you fuse a martial artist and a manifester, you can give the new creature the physical Characteristics of the martial artitist and the mental Characteristics of the mentalist. The new creature can fight unarmed and use phenom with ease.",
                    "Control of the resulting creature is determined by an Opposed Willpower Check between the targets. The Opposed Willpower Check can be repeated on the End Phase after a number of hours have passed equal to the Degree of Difference. If the DoD is less than 10, then the personality of the loser will influence the actions of the new creature."
                ]
            },
